description: First generation 1967 Chevrolet Camaro SS/RS - project -  Bolero Red -Clean + Clear VA Title
Complete car minus four parts : 4bbl Carb. - Radiator - right Headlight Assy. - Orig. Wheels.
Garaged for last 20+ years - Some disassembly, all parts [except above] included.
SS/RS Package, all badges-emblems-chrome trim [chrome bumpers straight], RS lights etc. SS suspension.
4 Speed Muncie M-22 rock crusher transmission w/ Hurst Competition Plus Shifter.
Original L-35  396 cu. in. Engine with Edelbrock alum. intake manifold. Engine does have VIN stamped on.
Original 12 bolt Positraction differential. not sure of gear ratio.
Original Muncie M-21 4 Speed transmission [one gear bad] -boxed up in the trunk, with original shifter.
Purchased in 1981, drove 1 year, parked in 1982 - car in running condition when parked.
Has misc. rust in body, rear quarter panels, trunk lid, and at rear window. Trunk floor needs replacement.
Has all glass, rear window hazy glass.
